title: Zucchini and Dill Frittata
directions: Preheat the broiler. Heat a 10inch nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add the butter and zucchini, cook for 5 minutes stirring occasionally. Add the scallions and cook for 3 more minutes or until zucchini is tender. /p In a medium bowl,whisk eggs, egg whites, water, dill, salt, pepper, and 2 tablespoons cheese. Add to the skillet and cook for 5 minutes, occasionally lifting the sides with a spatula and tilting the pan to allow uncooked egg to run underneath. /p The eggs will be set on the bottom but moist on the top, remove from the heat and sprinkle with the remaining cheese. /p Wrap the skillet handle with double the thickness of foil. Broil approximately 4” from the heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until eggs are set on the top. Cut into 4 pieces and serve immediately. /p Serving size: ¼ of pan  /p Calories: 143/serving
